Title: 1. Iron Man
Content: After being held captive in an Afghan cave, billionaire engineer Tony Stark creates a unique weaponized suit of armor to fight evil.

Title: 2. The Incredible Hulk
Content: Bruce Banner, a scientist on the run from the U.S. Government, must find a cure for the monster he turns into whenever he loses his temper.

Title: 3. Iron Man 2
Content: With the world now aware of his identity as Iron Man, Tony Stark must contend with both his declining health and a vengeful mad man with ties to his father's legacy.

Title: 4. Thor
Content: The powerful but arrogant god Thor is cast out of Asgard to live amongst humans in Midgard (Earth), where he soon becomes one of their finest defenders.

Title: 5. Captain America: The First Avenger
Content: Steve Rogers, a rejected military soldier, transforms into Captain America after taking a dose of a "Super-Soldier serum". But being Captain America comes at a price as he attempts to take down a warmonger and a terrorist organization.

Title: 6. Avengers Assemble
Content: Earth's mightiest heroes must come together and learn to fight as a team if they are going to stop the mischievous Loki and his alien army from enslaving humanity.

Title: 7. Iron Man 3
Content: When Tony Stark's world is torn apart by a formidable terrorist called the Mandarin, he starts an odyssey of rebuilding and retribution.

Title: 8. Thor: The Dark World
Content: When the Dark Elves attempt to plunge the universe into darkness, Thor must embark on a perilous and personal journey that will reunite him with doctor Jane Foster.

Title: 9. Captain America: The Winter Soldier
Content: As Steve Rogers struggles to embrace his role in the modern world, he teams up with a fellow Avenger and S.H.I.E.L.D agent, Black Widow, to battle a new threat from history: an assassin known as the Winter Soldier.

Title: 10. Guardians of the Galaxy
Content: A group of intergalactic criminals must pull together to stop a fanatical warrior with plans to purge the universe.

Title: 11. Avengers: Age of Ultron
Content: When Tony Stark and Bruce Banner try to jump-start a dormant peacekeeping program called Ultron, things go horribly wrong and it's up to Earth's mightiest heroes to stop the villainous Ultron from enacting his terrible plan.

Title: 12. Ant-Man
Content: Armed with a super-suit with the astonishing ability to shrink in scale but increase in strength, cat burglar Scott Lang must embrace his inner hero and help his mentor, Dr. Hank Pym, pull off a plan that will save the world.

Title: 13. Captain America: Civil War
Content: Political involvement in the Avengers' affairs causes a rift between Captain America and Iron Man.

Title: 14. Doctor Strange
Content: While on a journey of physical and spiritual healing, a brilliant neurosurgeon is drawn into the world of the mystic arts.

Title: 15. Guardians of the Galaxy: Vol. 2
Content: The Guardians struggle to keep together as a team while dealing with their personal family issues, notably Star-Lord's encounter with his father, the ambitious celestial being Ego.

Title: 16. Spider-Man: Homecoming
Content: Peter Parker tries to stop Adrian 'The Vulture' Toomes from selling weapons made with advanced Chitauri technology while trying to balance his life as an ordinary high school student.

Title: 17. Thor: Ragnarok
Content: Imprisoned on the planet Sakaar, Thor must race against time to return to Asgard and stop Ragnar√∂k, the destruction of his world, at the hands of the powerful and ruthless villain Hela.

Title: 18. Black Panther
Content: T'Challa, heir to the hidden but advanced kingdom of Wakanda, must step forward to lead his people into a new future and must confront a challenger from his country's past.

Title: 19. Avengers: Infinity War
Content: The Avengers and their allies must be willing to sacrifice all in an attempt to defeat the powerful Thanos before his blitz of devastation and ruin puts an end to the universe.

Title: 20. Ant-Man and the Wasp
Content: As Scott Lang balances being both a superhero and a father, Hope van Dyne and Dr. Hank Pym present an urgent new mission that finds the Ant-Man fighting alongside The Wasp to uncover secrets from their past.

Title: 21. Captain Marvel
Content: Carol Danvers becomes one of the universe's most powerful heroes when Earth is caught in the middle of a galactic war between two alien races.

Title: 22. Avengers: Endgame
Content: After the devastating events of Avengers: Infinity War (2018), the universe is in ruins. With the help of remaining allies, the Avengers assemble once more in order to reverse Thanos' actions and restore balance to the universe.

Title: 23. Spider-Man: Far from Home
Content: Peter Parker, the beloved superhero Spider-Man, faces four destructive elemental monsters while on holiday in Europe. Soon, he receives help from Mysterio, a fellow hero with mysterious origins.

Title: 24. Guardians of the Galaxy Vol. 3
Content: Still reeling from the loss of Gamora, Peter Quill rallies his team to defend the universe and one of their own - a mission that could mean the end of the Guardians if not successful.

Title: 25. Black Widow
Content: Natasha Romanoff confronts the darker parts of her ledger when a dangerous conspiracy with ties to her past arises.

Title: 1. Snow White and the Seven Dwarfs
Content: This is a list of films from Walt Disney Animation Studios and formerly known as Walt Disney Feature Animation, Walt Disney Productions and Disney Brothers Cartoon Studio, which creates animated feature films for The Walt Disney Company.

Title: 2. Pinocchio
Content: Exiled into the dangerous forest by her wicked stepmother, a princess is rescued by seven dwarf miners who make her part of their household.

Title: 3. Fantasia
Content: A living puppet, with the help of a cricket as his conscience, must prove himself worthy to become a real boy.

Title: 4. Dumbo
Content: A series of eight famous pieces of classical music, conducted by Leopold Stokowski and interpreted in animation by Walt Disney's team of artists.

Title: 5. Bambi
Content: Ridiculed because of his enormous ears, a young circus elephant is assisted by a mouse to achieve his full potential.

Title: 6. Saludos Amigos
Content: The story of a young deer growing up in the forest.

Title: 7. The Three Caballeros
Content: Disney animators tour South America and present four animated shorts inspired by their trip.

Title: 8. Make Mine Music
Content: Donald receives his birthday gifts, which include traditional gifts and information about Brazil (hosted by Z√© Carioca) and Mexico (by Panchito, a Mexican Charro Rooster).

Title: 9. Fun & Fancy Free
Content: Animation done to contemporary popular music.

Title: 10. Melody Time
Content: Jiminy Cricket hosts two Disney animated shorts: "Bongo," about a circus bear escaping to the wild, and "Mickey and the Beanstalk," a take on the famous fairy tale.

Title: 11. The Adventures of Ichabod and Mr. Toad
Content: An anthology of animated vignettes set to contemporary music.

Title: 12. Cinderella
Content: An animated adaptation of "The Wind in the Willows" followed by an adaptation of "The Legend of Sleepy Hollow".

Title: 13. Alice in Wonderland
Content: When Cinderella's cruel stepmother prevents her from attending the Royal Ball, she gets some unexpected help from the lovable mice Gus and Jaq and from her Fairy Godmother.

Title: 14. Peter Pan
Content: Alice stumbles into the world of Wonderland. Will she get home? Not if the Queen of Hearts has her way.

Title: 15. Lady and the Tramp
Content: Wendy and her brothers are whisked away to the magical world of Neverland with the hero of their stories, Peter Pan.

Title: 16. Sleeping Beauty
Content: The romantic tale of a sheltered uptown Cocker Spaniel dog and a streetwise downtown Mutt.

Title: 17. 101 Dalmatians
Content: After being snubbed by the royal family, a malevolent fairy places a curse on a princess which only a prince can break, along with the help of three good fairies.

Title: 18. The Sword in the Stone
Content: When a litter of Dalmatian puppies are abducted by the minions of Cruella De Vil, the owners must find them before she uses them for a diabolical fashion statement.

Title: 19. The Jungle Book
Content: A poor boy named Arthur learns the power of love, kindness, knowledge and bravery with the help of a wizard called Merlin in the path to become one of the most beloved kings in English history.

Title: 20. The AristoCats
Content: Bagheera the Panther and Baloo the Bear have a difficult time trying to convince a boy to leave the jungle for human civilization.

Title: 21. Robin Hood
Content: With the help of a smooth talking tomcat, a family of Parisian felines set to inherit a fortune from their owner try to make it back home after a jealous butler kidnaps them and leaves them in the country.

Title: 22. The Many Adventures of Winnie the Pooh
Content: The story of the legendary British outlaw portrayed with the characters as anthropomorphic animals.

Title: 23. The Rescuers
Content: In this collection of animated shorts based on the stories and characters by A.A. Milne, Winnie the Pooh, a honey-loving teddy bear, embarks on some eccentric adventures.

Title: 24. The Fox and the Hound
Content: Two mice of the Rescue Aid Society search for a little girl kidnapped by unscrupulous treasure hunters.

Title: 1. The 40 Year-Old Virgin
Content: Goaded by his buddies, a nerdy guy who's never "done the deed" only finds the pressure mounting when he meets a single mother.

Title: 2. Anger Management
Content: Dave Buznik is a businessman who is wrongly sentenced to an anger management program, where he meets an aggressive instructor.

Title: 3. As Good as It Gets
Content: A single mother and waitress, a misanthropic author, and a gay artist form an unlikely friendship after the artist is assaulted in a robbery.

Title: 4. Beauty Shop
Content: A determined hairstylist (Queen Latifah) competes with her former boss (Kevin Bacon) after opening her own business in Atlanta.

Title: 5. Blazing Saddles
Content: In order to ruin a western town and steal their land, a corrupt politician appoints a black sheriff, who promptly becomes his most formidable adversary.

Title: 6. Caddyshack
Content: An exclusive golf course has to deal with a flatulent new member and a destructive dancing gopher.

Title: 7. Casino Royale
Content: In an early spy spoof, aging Sir James Bond comes out of retirement to take on SMERSH.

Title: 8. Click
Content: A workaholic architect finds a universal remote that allows him to fast-forward and rewind to different parts of his life. Complications arise when the remote starts to overrule his choices.

Title: 9. Deathtrap
Content: A struggling playwright invites a young writer to his home to discuss a script, but the meeting spirals into a deadly game of deception and betrayal.

Title: 10. The Devil Wears Prada
Content: A smart but sensible new graduate lands a job as an assistant to Miranda Priestly, the demanding editor-in-chief of a high fashion magazine.

Title: 11. Diary of a Mad Black Woman
Content: A couple's seemingly solid marriage begins to crumble when the wife discovers that her husband intends to divorce her.

Title: 12. The First Wives Club
Content: Reunited by the death of a college friend, three divorced women seek revenge on the husbands who left them for younger women.

Title: 13. A Fish Called Wanda
Content: In London, four very different people team up on a jewel heist, then try to double-cross one another for the loot, complicated by their efforts to fool the very proper barrister Archibald Leach.

Title: 14. The Full Monty
Content: Six unemployed steel workers form a male striptease act. The women cheer them on to go for "the full monty" - total nudity.

Title: 15. The Gods Must Be Crazy
Content: A comic allegory about a traveling Bushman who encounters modern civilization and its stranger aspects, including a clumsy scientist and a band of revolutionaries.

Title: 16. Guarding Tess
Content: A former U.S. First Lady wants a particular Secret Service agent to head her bodyguard detail, even though he can't stand her.

Title: 17. Hopscotch
Content: Grounded with a desk job by incompetent superiors, a clever CIA agent retires and writes a tell all memoir that will embarrass his bosses, prompting him to go on the run and elude them.

Title: 18. Legally Blonde
Content: Elle Woods, a fashionable sorority queen, is dumped by her boyfriend. She decides to follow him to law school. While she is there, she figures out that there is more to her than just looks.

Title: 19. Little Miss Sunshine
Content: A family determined to get their young daughter into the finals of a beauty pageant take a cross-country trip in their VW bus.

Title: 20. Monty Python and the Holy Grail
Content: King Arthur and his Knights of the Round Table embark on a surreal, low-budget search for the Holy Grail, encountering many, very silly obstacles.

Title: 21. My Cousin Vinny
Content: Two New Yorkers accused of murder in rural Alabama while on their way back to college call in the help of one of their cousins, a loudmouth lawyer with no trial experience.

Title: 22. A Night at the Opera
Content: A sly business manager and the wacky friends of two opera singers in Italy help them achieve success in America while humiliating their stuffy and snobbish enemies.

Title: 23. Patch Adams
Content: The true story of a heroic man, Hunter "Patch" Adams, determined to become a medical doctor because he enjoys helping people. He ventured where no doctor had ventured before, using humour and pathos.

Title: 1. Pitch Black
Content: A transport ship crashes and leaves its crew stranded on a desert planet inhabited by bloodthirsty creatures that come out during an eclipse.

Title: 2. Isn't She Great
Content: Bette Midler and Nathan Lane star in this comedy about Jacqueline Susann, the ambitious woman of dubious talent who wrote Valley of the Dolls, a best-selling novel that became a sensation.

Title: 3. Erin Brockovich
Content: An unemployed single mother becomes a legal assistant and almost single-handedly brings down a California power company accused of polluting a city's water supply.

Title: 4. The Skulls
Content: A senior at an ivy league college, who depends on scholarships and working on the side, gets accepted into the secret society The Skulls. He hopes it betters chances at Harvard but The Skulls is not what he thought and comes at a price.

Title: 5. U-571
Content: A German submarine is boarded by disguised American submariners trying to capture their Enigma cipher machine.

Title: 6. The Flintstones in Viva Rock Vegas
Content: In this live-action prequel to The Flintstones (1994), the Flintstones and the Rubbles go on a trip to Rock Vegas, where Wilma Slaghoople is pursued by playboy Chip Rockefeller.

Title: 7. Gladiator
Content: A former Roman General sets out to exact vengeance against the corrupt emperor who murdered his family and sent him into slavery.

Title: 8. Screwed
Content: A chauffeur kidnaps his rich boss's dog to hold it for ransom, but when she accidentally gets the dog back, she thinks that it's the chauffeur who's been kidnapped.

Title: 9. The Adventures of Rocky & Bullwinkle
Content: When enemies Boris, Natasha, and Fearless Leader escape into the real world with a nefarious scheme, Rocky and Bullwinkle do the same, and team up with a young F.B.I. Agent to stop the trio.

Title: 10. Nutty Professor II: The Klumps
Content: Scientist Sherman Klump's inventions, his upcoming marriage to his pretty colleague Denise Gaines, and his reputation, are threatened by his evil clone Buddy Love.

Title: 11. Bring It On
Content: A champion high school cheerleading squad discovers its previous captain stole all their best routines from an inner-city school and must scramble to compete at this year's championships.

Title: 12. The Watcher
Content: David Allen Griffin is a cool killer- time and time again, he chooses a female victim, studies her for weeks till he knows her routine to the smallest detail, makes meticulous preparations using his forensic knowledge to gain entry when she's quite alone, subdues her and administers a long, torturous death. Joel Campbell got so frustrated by his failure to capture Griffin in Los Angeles, that he quit the FBI, moved to Chicago, and remains in psychiatric therapy, unable to function normally. Then he realizes, when opening his mail very late, that a new murder victim is Griffin's, and the killer sent him pictures of her. Campbell reports this to the police, but is unwilling to join them in the search, suggesting Griffin is too slick and clever; yet he won't get out of it that easily.

Title: 13. Meet the Parents
Content: Chicago male nurse and chronic under-achiever Greg Focker meets his charming teacher girlfriend Pam Byrnes' parents Jack and Dina before proposing, but suspicious Jack is an overprotective former CIA agent - every date's worst nightmare.

Title: 14. How the Grinch Stole Christmas
Content: On the outskirts of Whoville lives a green, revenge-seeking Grinch who plans to ruin Christmas for all of the citizens of the town.

Title: 15. O Brother, Where Art Thou?
Content: In the deep south during the 1930s, three escaped convicts search for hidden treasure while a relentless lawman pursues them.

Title: 16. The Family Man
Content: A fast-lane investment broker, offered the opportunity to see how the other half lives, wakes up to find that his sports car and girlfriend have become a mini-van and wife.

Title: 17. Head Over Heels
Content: A young woman is attracted to a man despite her thinking she's seen him kill someone.

Title: 18. Hannibal
Content: Living in exile, Dr. Hannibal Lecter tries to reconnect with now disgraced F.B.I. Agent Clarice Starling, and finds himself a target for revenge from a powerful victim.

Title: 19. Josie and the Pussycats
Content: A girl group find themselves in the middle of a conspiracy to deliver subliminal messages through popular music.

Title: 20. Bridget Jones's Diary
Content: Bridget Jones is determined to improve herself while she looks for love in a year in which she keeps a personal diary.

Title: 21. The Mummy Returns
Content: The mummified body of Imhotep is shipped to a museum in London, where he once again wakes and begins his campaign of rage and terror.

Title: 22. The Fast and the Furious
Content: Los Angeles police officer Brian O'Conner must decide where his loyalty really lies when he becomes enamored with the street racing world he has been sent undercover to end it.

Title: 23. Jurassic Park III
Content: A decidedly odd couple with ulterior motives convince Dr. Grant to go to Isla Sorna for a holiday, but their unexpected landing startles the island's new inhabitants.

Title: 24. American Pie 2
Content: Jim and his friends are now in college, and they decide to meet up at the beach house for some fun.

Title: 25. Captain Corelli's Mandolin
Content: When a fisherman leaves to fight with the Greek army during World War II, his fianc√©e falls in love with the local Italian commander.

Title: 1. Skyfall
Content: James Bond's loyalty to M is tested when her past comes back to haunt her. When MI6 comes under attack, 007 must track down and destroy the threat, no matter how personal the cost.

Title: 2. Spider-Man 3
Content: A strange black entity from another world bonds with Peter Parker and causes inner turmoil as he contends with new villains, temptations, and revenge.

Title: 3. Spectre
Content: A cryptic message from James Bond's past sends him on a trail to uncover the existence of a sinister organisation named SPECTRE. With a new threat dawning, Bond learns the terrible truth about the author of all his pain in his most recent missions.

Title: 4. Spider-Man
Content: After being bitten by a genetically-modified spider, a shy teenager gains spider-like abilities that he uses to fight injustice as a masked superhero and face a vengeful enemy.

Title: 5. Spider-Man 2
Content: Peter Parker is beset with troubles in his failing personal life as he battles a former brilliant scientist named Otto Octavius.
A frustrated writer struggles to keep his family alive when a series of global catastrophes threatens to annihilate mankind.

Title: 7. The Da Vinci Code
Content: A murder inside the Louvre, and clues in Da Vinci paintings, lead to the discovery of a religious mystery protected by a secret society for two thousand years, which could shake the foundations of Christianity.

Title: 8. The Amazing Spider-Man
Content: After Peter Parker is bitten by a genetically altered spider, he gains newfound, spider-like powers and ventures out to save the city from the machinations of a mysterious reptilian foe.

Title: 9. The Amazing Spider-Man 2
Content: When New York is put under siege by Oscorp, it is up to Spider-Man to save the city he swore to protect as well as his loved ones.

Title: 10. Hancock
Content: Hancock is a superhero whose ill-considered behavior regularly causes damage in the millions. He changes when the person he saves helps him improve his public image.

Title: 11. Men in Black 3
Content: Agent J travels in time to M.I.B.'s early days in 1969 to stop an alien from assassinating his friend Agent K and changing history.

Title: 12. Casino Royale
Content: After earning a licence to kill, secret agent James Bond sets out on his first mission as 007. Bond must defeat a private banker funding terrorists in a high-stakes game of poker at Casino Royale, in Montenegro.

Title: 13. Men in Black
Content: James, an NYC cop, is hired by Agent K of a secret government agency that monitors extraterrestrial life on Earth. Together, they must recover an item that has been stolen by an intergalactic villain.

Title: 14. Quantum of Solace
Content: James Bond tries to stop an organisation from eliminating a country's most valuable resource.

Title: 15. The Smurfs
Content: When the evil wizard Gargamel chases the tiny blue Smurfs out of their village, they tumble from their magical world into New York City.

Title: 16. The Mermaid
Content: Shan, a mermaid, is sent to assassinate Xuan, a developer who threatens the ecosystem of her race, but ends up falling in love with him instead.

Title: 17. Terminator 2: Judgment Day
Content: A cyborg, identical to the one who failed to kill Sarah Connor, must now protect her ten year old son John from an even more advanced and powerful cyborg.

Title: 18. Angels & Demons
Content: Harvard symbologist Robert Langdon works with a nuclear physicist to solve a murder and prevent a terrorist act against the Vatican during one of the significant events within the church.

Title: 19. Hotel Transylvania 2
Content: Dracula and his friends try to bring out the monster in his half human, half vampire grandson in order to keep Mavis from leaving the hotel.

Title: 20. Men in Black II
Content: Agent J is sent to find Agent K and restore his memory after the re-appearance of a case from K's past.

Title: 21. Die Another Day
Content: James Bond is sent to investigate the connection between a North Korean terrorist and a diamond mogul, who is funding the development of an international space weapon.

Title: 22. Dances with Wolves
Content: Lieutenant John Dunbar, assigned to a remote western Civil War outpost, finds himself engaging with a neighbouring Sioux settlement, causing him to question his own purpose.

Title: 23. Gone with the Wind
Content: A sheltered and manipulative Southern belle and a roguish profiteer face off in a turbulent romance as the society around them crumbles with the end of slavery and is rebuilt during the Civil War and Reconstruction periods.

Title: 24. Godzilla
Content: French nuclear tests irradiate an iguana into a giant monster that heads off to New York City. The American military must chase the monster across the city to stop it before it reproduces.

Title: 25. Hitch
Content: A smooth-talking man falls for a hardened columnist while helping a shy accountant woo a beautiful heiress.

Title: 1. Solaris
Content: A troubled psychologist is sent to investigate the crew of an isolated research station orbiting a bizarre planet.

Title: 2. Rising Sun
Content: When an escort girl is found dead in the offices of a Japanese company in Los Angeles, detectives Web Smith and John Connor act as liaison between the company's executives and the investigating cop Tom Graham.

Title: 3. Ice Age: Dawn of the Dinosaurs
Content: When Sid's attempt to adopt three dinosaur eggs gets him abducted by their real mother to an underground lost world, his friends attempt to rescue him.

Title: 4. Home Alone
Content: An eight-year-old troublemaker, mistakenly left home alone, must defend his home against a pair of burglars on Christmas Eve.

Title: 5. Home Alone 2: Lost in New York
Content: Kevin accidentally boards a flight to New York City and gets separated from his family who are on their way to Miami. He then bumps into two of his old enemies, who plan to rob a toy store.

Title: 6. Prometheus
Content: Following clues to the origin of mankind, a team finds a structure on a distant moon, but they soon realize they are not alone.

Title: 7. X-Men
Content: In a world where mutants (evolved super-powered humans) exist and are discriminated against, two groups form for an inevitable clash: the supremacist Brotherhood, and the pacifist X-Men.

Title: 8. X-Men 2
Content: When anti-mutant Colonel William Stryker kidnaps Professor X and attacks his school, the X-Men must ally with their archenemy Magneto to stop him.

Title: 9. X-Men: The Last Stand
Content: The human government develops a cure for mutations, and Jean Grey becomes a darker uncontrollable persona called the Phoenix who allies with Magneto, causing escalation into an all-out battle for the X-Men.

Title: 10. Alien
Content: After investigating a mysterious transmission of unknown origin, the crew of a commercial spacecraft encounters a deadly lifeform.

Title: 11. The A-Team
Content: A group of Iraq War veterans look to clear their name with the U.S. Military, who suspect the four men of committing a crime for which they were framed.

Title: 12. Minority Report
Content: John works with the PreCrime police which stop crimes before they take place, with the help of three 'PreCogs' who can foresee crimes. Events ensue when John finds himself framed for a future murder.

Title: 13. Aliens
Content: Decades after surviving the Nostromo incident, Ellen Ripley is sent out to re-establish contact with a terraforming colony but finds herself battling the Alien Queen and her offspring.

Title: 14. Avatar
Content: A paraplegic Marine dispatched to the moon Pandora on a unique mission becomes torn between following his orders and protecting the world he feels is his home.

Title: 15. There's Something About Mary
Content: A man gets a chance to meet up with his dream girl from high school, even though his date with her back then was a complete disaster.

Title: 16. Lincoln
Content: As the Civil War rages on, U.S President Abraham Lincoln struggles with continuing carnage on the battlefield as he fights with many inside his own cabinet on his decision to emancipate the slaves.

Title: 17. The Wolverine
Content: Wolverine comes to Japan to meet an old friend whose life he saved years ago, and gets embroiled in a conspiracy involving yakuza and mutants.

Title: 18. Gulliver's Travels
Content: Travel writer Lemuel Gulliver takes an assignment in Bermuda but ends up on the island of Lilliput, where he towers over its tiny citizens.

Title: 19. Rise of the Planet of the Apes
Content: A substance designed to help the brain repair itself gives advanced intelligence to a chimpanzee who leads an ape uprising.

Title: 20. Independence Day
Content: The aliens are coming and their goal is to invade and destroy Earth. Fighting superior technology, mankind's best weapon is the will to survive.

Title: 21. Cast Away
Content: A FedEx executive undergoes a physical and emotional transformation after crash landing on a deserted island.

Title: 22. Die Hard 4.0
Content: John McClane and a young hacker join forces to take down master cyber-terrorist Thomas Gabriel in Washington D.C.

Title: 23. Romeo + Juliet
Content: Shakespeare's famous play is updated to the hip modern suburb of Verona still retaining its original dialogue.

Title: 24. Predators
Content: A group of elite warriors parachute into an unfamiliar jungle and are hunted by members of a merciless alien race.

Title: 2. Inception
Content: When the menace known as the Joker wreaks havoc and chaos on the people of Gotham, Batman, James Gordon and Harvey Dent must work together to put an end to the madness.

Title: 3. The Matrix
Content: A thief who steals corporate secrets through the use of dream-sharing technology is given the inverse task of planting an idea into the mind of a C.E.O., but his tragic past may doom the project and his team to disaster.

Title: 4. GoodFellas
Content: When a beautiful stranger leads computer hacker Neo to a forbidding underworld, he discovers the shocking truth--the life he knows is the elaborate deception of an evil cyber-intelligence.

Title: 5. The Green Mile
Content: The story of Henry Hill and his life in the mafia, covering his relationship with his wife Karen and his mob partners Jimmy Conway and Tommy DeVito.

Title: 6. Interstellar
Content: A tale set on death row, where gentle giant John Coffey possesses the mysterious power to heal people's ailments. When the lead guard, Paul Edgecombe, recognizes John's gift, he tries to help stave off the condemned man's execution.

Title: 7. The Departed
Content: When Earth becomes uninhabitable in the future, a farmer and ex-NASA pilot, Joseph Cooper, is tasked to pilot a spacecraft, along with a team of researchers, to find a new planet for humans.

Title: 8. The Prestige
Content: An undercover cop and a mole in the police attempt to identify each other while infiltrating an Irish gang in South Boston.

Title: 9. Casablanca
Content: After a tragic accident, two stage magicians in 1890s London engage in a battle to create the ultimate illusion while sacrificing everything they have to outwit each other.

Title: 10. Joker
Content: A cynical expatriate American cafe owner struggles to decide whether or not to help his former lover and her fugitive husband escape the Nazis in French Morocco.

Title: 11. The Shining
Content: Arthur Fleck, a party clown and a failed stand-up comedian, leads an impoverished life with his ailing mother. However, when society shuns him and brands him as a freak, he decides to embrace the life of crime and chaos in Gotham City.

Title: 12. The Dark Knight Rises
Content: A family heads to an isolated hotel for the winter, where a sinister presence influences the father into violence. At the same time, his psychic son sees horrifying forebodings from both the past and the future.

Title: 13. Once Upon a Time in America
Content: Bane, an imposing terrorist, attacks Gotham City and disrupts its eight-year-long period of peace. This forces Bruce Wayne to come out of hiding and don the cape and cowl of Batman again.

Title: 14. Full Metal Jacket
Content: A former Prohibition-era Jewish gangster returns to the Lower East Side of Manhattan 35 years later, where he must once again confront the ghosts and regrets of his old life.

Title: 15. A Clockwork Orange
Content: A pragmatic U.S. Marine observes the dehumanizing effects the Vietnam War has on his fellow recruits from their brutal boot camp training to the bloody street fighting in Hue.

Title: 16. Heat
Content: Alex DeLarge and his droogs barbarize a decaying near-future.

Title: 17. L.A. Confidential
Content: A group of high-end professional thieves start to feel the heat from the LAPD when they unknowingly leave a verbal clue at their latest heist.

Title: 18. Batman Begins
Content: As corruption grows in 1950s Los Angeles, three policemen - one strait-laced, one brutal, and one sleazy - investigate a series of murders with their own brand of justice.

Title: 19. Unforgiven
Content: After witnessing his parents' death, Bruce learns the art of fighting to confront injustice. When he returns to Gotham as Batman, he must stop a secret society that intends to destroy the city.

Title: 20. The Treasure of the Sierra Madre
Content: Retired Old West gunslinger William Munny reluctantly takes on one last job, with the help of his old partner Ned Logan and a young man, The "Schofield Kid."

Title: 21. Dial M for Murder
Content: Two down-on-their-luck Americans searching for work in 1920s Mexico convince an old prospector to help them mine for gold in the Sierra Madre Mountains.

Title: 22. V for Vendetta
Content: A former tennis star arranges the murder of his adulterous wife.

Title: 23. Blade Runner
Content: In a future British dystopian society, a shadowy freedom fighter, known only by the alias of "V", plots to overthrow the tyrannical government - with the help of a young woman.

Title: 24. Gran Torino
Content: A blade runner must pursue and terminate four replicants who stole a ship in space and have returned to Earth to find their creator.

Title: 25. Barry Lyndon
Content: After a Hmong teenager tries to steal his prized 1972 Gran Torino, a disgruntled, prejudiced Korean War veteran seeks to redeem both the boy and himself.

Title: 26. Mad Max: Fury Road
Content: An Irish rogue wins the heart of a rich widow and assumes her dead husband's aristocratic position in 18th-century England.

Title: 27. Million Dollar Baby
Content: In a post-apocalyptic wasteland, a woman rebels against a tyrannical ruler in search for her homeland with the aid of a group of female prisoners, a psychotic worshipper and a drifter named Max.

Title: 28. Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows: Part 2
Content: Frankie, an ill-tempered old coach, reluctantly agrees to train aspiring boxer Maggie. Impressed with her determination and talent, he helps her become the best and the two soon form a close bond.

Title: 29. Before Sunset
Content: Harry, Ron, and Hermione search for Voldemort's remaining Horcruxes in their effort to destroy the Dark Lord as the final battle rages on at Hogwarts.

Title: 1. Antz
Content: A rather neurotic ant tries to break from his totalitarian society while trying to win the affection of the princess he loves.

Title: 2. The Prince of Egypt
Content: Egyptian Prince Moses learns of his identity as a Hebrew and his destiny to become the chosen deliverer of his people.

Title: 3. Chicken Run
Content: When a cockerel apparently flies into a chicken farm, the chickens see him as an opportunity to escape their evil owners.

Title: 4. The Road to El Dorado
Content: Two swindlers get their hands on a map to the fabled city of gold, El Dorado.

Title: 5. Joseph: King of Dreams
Content: A prophet who has the ability to interpret dreams is sold into slavery in Egypt, where people learn of his gifts.

Title: 6. Shrek
Content: A mean lord exiles fairytale creatures to the swamp of a grumpy ogre, who must go on a quest and rescue a princess for the lord in order to get his land back.

Title: 7. Spirit: Stallion of the Cimarron
Content: A captured mustang remains determined to return to his herd no matter what.

Title: 8. Sinbad: Legend of the Seven Seas
Content: The sailor of legend is framed by the goddess Eris for the theft of the Book of Peace and must travel to her realm at the end of the world to retrieve it and save the life of his childhood friend Prince Proteus.

Title: 9. Shrek 2
Content: Shrek and Fiona travel to the Kingdom of Far Far Away, where Fiona's parents are King and Queen, to celebrate their marriage. When they arrive, they find they are not as welcome as they thought they would be.

Title: 10. Shark Tale
Content: When a son of a gangster shark boss is accidentally killed while on the hunt, his would-be prey and his vegetarian brother decide to use the incident to their own advantage.

Title: 11. Madagascar
Content: A group of animals who have spent all their life in a New York zoo end up in the jungles of Madagascar, and must adjust to living in the wild.

Title: 12. The Curse of the Were-Rabbit
Content: Wallace and his loyal dog, Gromit, set out to discover the mystery behind the garden sabotage that plagues their village and threatens the annual giant vegetable growing contest.

Title: 13. Over the Hedge
Content: A scheming raccoon fools a mismatched family of forest creatures into helping him repay a debt of food, by invading the new suburban sprawl that popped up while they were hibernating...and learns a lesson about family himself.

Title: 14. Flushed Away
Content: The story of an uptown rat that gets flushed down the toilet from his penthouse apartment, ending in the sewers of London, where he has to learn a whole new and different way of life.

Title: 15. Shrek the Third
Content: Reluctantly designated as the heir to the land of Far, Far Away, Shrek hatches a plan to install the rebellious Artie as the new king while Princess Fiona tries to fend off a coup d'√©tat by the jilted Prince Charming.

Title: 16. Bee Movie
Content: Barry B. Benson, a bee just graduated from college, is disillusioned at his lone career choice: making honey. On a special trip outside the hive, Barry's life is saved by Vanessa, a florist in New York City. As their relationship blossoms, he discovers humans actually eat honey and subsequently decides to sue them.

Title: 17. Kung Fu Panda
Content: To everyone's surprise, including his own, Po, an overweight, clumsy panda, is chosen as protector of the Valley of Peace. His suitability will soon be tested as the valley's arch-enemy is on his way.

Title: 18. Madagascar: Escape 2 Africa
Content: The Madagascar animals fly back to New York City, but crash-land on an African nature reserve in Kenya, where they meet others of their own kind, and Alex especially discovers his royal heritage as prince of a lion pride.

Title: 19. How to Train Your Dragon
Content: A hapless young Viking who aspires to hunt dragons becomes the unlikely friend of a young dragon himself, and learns there may be more to the creatures than he assumed.

Title: 20. Monsters vs. Aliens
Content: A woman transformed into a giant after she is struck by a meteorite on her wedding day becomes part of a team of monsters sent in by the U.S. government to defeat an alien mastermind trying to take over Earth.

Title: 21. Shrek Forever After
Content: Rumpelstiltskin tricks a mid-life crisis burdened Shrek into allowing himself to be erased from existence and cast in a dark alternate timeline where Rumpelstiltskin rules supreme.

Title: 22. Megamind
Content: Evil genius Megamind finally defeats his do-gooder nemesis, Metro Man, but is left without a purpose in a superhero-free world.

Title: 23. Kung Fu Panda 2
Content: Po and his friends fight to stop a peacock villain from conquering China with a deadly new weapon, but first the Dragon Warrior must come to terms with his past.

Title: 24. Puss in Boots
Content: An outlaw cat, his childhood egg-friend, and a seductive thief kitty set out in search for the eggs of the fabled Golden Goose to clear his name, restore his lost honor, and regain the trust of his mother and town.

Title: 25. Madagascar 3: Europe's Most Wanted
Content: The Madagascar animals join a struggling European circus to get back to New York, but find themselves being pursued by a psychotic animal-control officer.

Title: 26. Rise of the Guardians
Content: When the evil spirit Pitch launches an assault on Earth, the Immortal Guardians team up to protect the innocence of children all around the world.

Title: 27. The Croods
Content: After their cave is destroyed, a caveman family must trek through an unfamiliar fantastical world with the help of an inventive boy.

Title: 28. Turbo
Content: A freak accident might just help an everyday garden snail achieve his biggest dream: winning the Indy 500.

Title: 29. Mr. Peabody & Sherman
Content: Sherman, a young boy, misuses a time machine made by his scientist father Mr. Peabody and causes the world history to go haywire. It is now up to Mr. Peabody to rescue his son and the world.

Title: 30. How to Train Your Dragon 2
Content: When Hiccup and Toothless discover an ice cave that is home to hundreds of new wild dragons and the mysterious Dragon Rider, the two friends find themselves at the center of a battle to protect the peace.

Title: 31. Penguins of Madagascar
Content: Skipper, Kowalski, Rico and Private join forces with undercover organization The North Wind to stop the villainous Dr. Octavius Brine from destroying the world as we know it.

Title: 32. Home
Content: Oh, a lovable misfit alien, runs away from his planet and takes shelter on Earth, where he befriends Tip, an adventurous young girl who is on a quest to find her displaced mother Lucy.

Title: 33. Kung Fu Panda 3
Content: Continuing his "legendary adventures of awesomeness", Po must face two hugely epic, but different threats: one supernatural and the other a little closer to home.

Title: 34. Trolls
Content: After the Bergens invade Troll Village, Poppy, the happiest Troll ever born, and the curmudgeonly Branch set off on a journey to rescue her friends.

Title: 35. The Boss Baby
Content: A suit-wearing, briefcase-carrying baby pairs up with his 7-year old brother to stop the dastardly plot of the CEO of Puppy Co.

Title: 36. Captain Underpants: The First Epic Movie
Content: Two overly-imaginative pranksters hypnotize their grumpy principal into thinking he's a ridiculously enthusiastic, incredibly dimwitted, underwear-themed superhero.

Title: 37. How to Train Your Dragon: The Hidden World
Content: When Hiccup discovers Toothless isn't the only Night Fury, he must seek the Hidden World, a secret Dragon Utopia before a hired tyrant named Grimmel finds it first.

Title: 38. Trolls World Tour
Content: When the Queen of the Hard Rock Trolls tries to take over all the Troll kingdoms, Queen Poppy and her friends try different ways to save all the Trolls.

Title: 39. The Croods: A New Age
Content: The prehistoric family the Croods are challenged by a rival family the Bettermans, who claim to be better and more evolved.

Title: 40. The Boss Baby 2: Family Business
Content: The Templeton brothers have become adults and drifted away from each other, but a new boss baby with a cutting-edge approach is about to bring them together again - and inspire a new family business.
